\int \tan(x) dx
\int\sin(x)\cdot\cos(x)^{-1} dx
-\ln(\cos(x))+\int\frac{\cos(x)\cdot\ln(\cos(x))}{\sin(x)} dx
u=\cos x
du=-\sin xdx
\int \tan x\, dx=-\int\frac{du}u
u=\cos x
du=-\sin x~dx
\int\tan x~dx=-\int\frac{du}u\;.
\int \tan xdx=\int\frac{\sec x\tan xdx}{\sec x}
\sec x=z, dz=\sec x\tan x dx
\int\frac{\sec x\tan xdx}{\sec x}=\int\frac{dz}z=\log |z|+C=\log|\sec x|+C=-\log|\cos x|+C
